789
00:51:33,060 --> 00:51:36,171
The same sunlight that lets us see
the world for what it really is.

790
00:51:40,480 --> 00:51:41,969
Blue's a weird color.

791
00:51:45,040 --> 00:51:48,928
Come to think of it, Cobalt's
not really blue either.

792
00:51:48,929 --> 00:51:50,783
At least not in its natural form.

793
00:51:52,080 --> 00:51:53,372
Yeah I know.

794
00:51:53,373 --> 00:51:55,493
We did the elements project
together in eighth grade.

795
00:51:56,286 --> 00:51:57,691
Oh yeah.

796
00:52:03,040 --> 00:52:05,339
Cobalt's kind of weird.

797
00:52:06,066 --> 00:52:11,607
I mean it's used in so many things
but too much of it is poisonous.

798
00:52:13,920 --> 00:52:16,782
But you could say a lot
of things are like that.

799
00:52:20,720 --> 00:52:21,720
Like drinking.

800
00:52:23,840 --> 00:52:27,183
A lot of people drink alcohol and
it lets them loosen up, but...

801
00:52:28,000 --> 00:52:31,840
too much of it and, you know
it could really mess your life up.

802
00:52:36,800 --> 00:52:38,609
You could even say it's like water.

803
00:52:40,560 --> 00:52:42,993
We're made of water, but...

804
00:52:42,994 --> 00:52:46,256
too much of that and you're
six feet underground.

805
00:52:46,257 --> 00:52:49,701
Or six feet under water if you
wanna take it literally.

806
00:52:52,560 --> 00:52:55,565
You could even say Cobalt's
kind of like dreams.

807
00:52:56,689 --> 00:52:59,364
We spend our whole lives chasing them,

808
00:52:59,680 --> 00:53:03,823
but at the end of the
road they just consume us.

809
00:53:03,824 --> 00:53:06,268
Turn us into different people.

810
00:53:07,520 --> 00:53:09,086
Like dreams.

811
00:53:12,800 --> 00:53:14,699
Shoot, what time is it?

812
00:53:20,640 --> 00:53:23,729
I gotta go. I got work soon.

813
00:53:23,730 --> 00:53:25,164
Hey do you know where I left my bike?

814
00:53:25,165 --> 00:53:27,076
Yeah you lived in the side yard.

815
00:53:27,077 --> 00:53:28,734
Why didn't you tell me you got a job?

816
00:53:28,735 --> 00:53:30,581
I must have just forgotten, yeah.

817
00:53:30,582 --> 00:53:32,266
That's cool dude. Gotta love a working man.

818
00:53:32,267 --> 00:53:35,333
- Eh, I mean I just need some extra money for college you know.
- Yeah.

819
00:53:35,334 --> 00:53:37,522
Don't worry, we're still
focusing on the film.

820
00:53:37,523 --> 00:53:39,653
You should get a job too.

821
00:53:39,654 --> 00:53:42,803
Can't you work at your
parents'... your store?

822
00:53:43,011 --> 00:53:45,084
Yeah, no I'm not gonna work there.

823
00:53:47,680 --> 00:53:50,026
Um, so I'll see you tomorrow then?

824
00:53:50,027 --> 00:53:52,743
No I can't I have an
orientation up in norcal.

825
00:53:52,744 --> 00:53:55,124
And then I have work all day the next day.

826
00:53:55,125 --> 00:53:56,639
So how about the next day?

827
00:53:56,640 --> 00:53:58,000
Yeah that can work, okay for sure.

828
00:53:58,640 --> 00:53:59,613
Alright then, see you man.

829
00:53:59,614 --> 00:54:01,189
- Alright, see you.
- Good luck at work.

830
00:54:01,190 --> 00:54:04,881
- Thank you. Side gate's unlocked right?
- Yep.

831
00:54:31,200 --> 00:54:33,146
Like dreams.

832
00:54:40,400 --> 00:54:41,469
What's up?

833
00:54:41,470 --> 00:54:44,541
Hey Tommy. We're gonna cancel filming
tomorrow and the next day.

834
00:54:44,542 --> 00:54:48,452
Johnny just told me that he has some stuff to do
so we're gonna push back filming a couple days.

835
00:54:48,880 --> 00:54:51,374
Yeah, he let me know.

836
00:54:52,036 --> 00:54:56,062
Oh. Okay uh cool. Well I just
wanted to make sure, you know.

837
00:54:56,393 --> 00:54:58,360
Got it boss. Have a good night.

838
00:54:58,361 --> 00:55:01,037
Yeah you too man, thanks.

839
00:55:04,160 --> 00:55:07,308
Like Will said, the film
needs to be perfect.

840
00:55:07,309 --> 00:55:10,639
This created a new drive in
me that I never had before.

841
00:55:10,640 --> 00:55:12,299
It scared me.

842
00:55:12,300 --> 00:55:14,129
It was my first mistake.

843
00:55:14,130 --> 00:55:19,126
They say method acting consumes the soul of the actor
and transforms them into a character they're playing.

844
00:55:19,127 --> 00:55:21,473
Into someone they're not.

845
00:55:21,474 --> 00:55:25,273
Apparently method directing
isn't really defined yet.

846
00:55:25,274 --> 00:55:26,700
So I decided to try it.

847
00:56:47,760 --> 00:56:49,261
Hey what's up Johnny?

848
00:56:49,262 --> 00:56:51,679
Sorry, I'mma be a little late today.

849
00:56:51,680 --> 00:56:53,974
That's cool. No worries, uh how come?

850
00:56:53,975 --> 00:56:55,490
Can't find my bike.

851
00:56:55,491 --> 00:56:59,155
Oh... that's weird. Do you
need me to pick you up?

852
00:57:00,400 --> 00:57:03,885
No, thanks though. I was...
I was just letting you know.

853
00:57:03,886 --> 00:57:06,264
Okay, uh see you soon man.

854
00:57:06,265 --> 00:57:07,835
See ya.

855
00:57:11,120 --> 00:57:12,120
Okay.

856
00:57:12,666 --> 00:57:13,395
Action.

857
00:57:13,396 --> 00:57:15,309
Yeah I'm no idiot, Han.

858
00:57:15,310 --> 00:57:17,790
You better give me back the rest
of my money or I'll kill you.

859
00:57:21,920 --> 00:57:25,840
Just give me back the rest of my share.

860
00:57:28,960 --> 00:57:32,926
Dude that was the best one yet. So close.

861
00:57:34,281 --> 00:57:35,620
Damn it!

862
00:57:36,387 --> 00:57:37,917
Was it good enough though?

863
00:57:37,918 --> 00:57:41,537
Yes, but good enough isn't 'good enough.'

864
00:57:41,538 --> 00:57:43,491
Please. I'm a little sick, too.

865
00:57:43,492 --> 00:57:45,957
Better stay across that table then
because I don't wanna catch anything.

866
00:57:45,958 --> 00:57:47,835
It's not contagious, don't worry.

867
00:57:50,160 --> 00:57:52,960
Uh are you a doctor?

868
00:57:55,416 --> 00:57:56,458
Exactly.

869
00:57:56,459 --> 00:57:57,829
Are we done?

870
00:57:58,800 --> 00:58:00,987
- Yes.
- Yes!

871
00:58:00,988 --> 00:58:03,440
But let's run it back one
more time for variety's sake.

872
00:58:06,080 --> 00:58:07,562
It's just one more.

873
00:58:07,563 --> 00:58:09,313
Come on dude it's gonna be the same.

874
00:58:09,314 --> 00:58:12,239
Just draw on how you felt...

875
00:58:12,240 --> 00:58:14,195
when you found out your bike was stolen.

876
00:58:16,480 --> 00:58:18,862
Wait, stolen?

877
00:58:18,863 --> 00:58:21,060
Yeah you said you couldn't find it.

878
00:58:23,043 --> 00:58:25,440
I never said it was stolen.

879
00:58:26,560 --> 00:58:29,452
Well just assuming it was

880
00:58:29,453 --> 00:58:32,154
Imagine how it felt.

881
00:58:32,155 --> 00:58:34,187
How it would feel.

882
00:58:35,708 --> 00:58:38,442
Well, okay, you got this bro.

883
00:58:38,443 --> 00:58:42,560
Remember, The Academy is watching, so.

884
00:58:42,561 --> 00:58:43,986
Ready?

885
00:58:43,987 --> 00:58:45,417
Okay.

886
00:58:45,418 --> 00:58:47,429
Action.

887
00:58:47,430 --> 00:58:49,627
I'm not an idiot.

888
00:58:49,628 --> 00:58:52,902
You can't just take what's not yours
and expect for nothing to happen.

889
00:58:53,840 --> 00:58:57,231
Listen I'm not gonna make
you return what's mine,

890
00:58:57,232 --> 00:58:59,952
but if we stray apart just
know it's because of you.

891
00:59:03,985 --> 00:59:05,261
- Oh my god.
- How's that?

892
00:59:05,262 --> 00:59:07,091
That's the one.

893
00:59:07,092 --> 00:59:10,767
It wasn't exactly a part of the
script but it worked even better.

894
00:59:12,552 --> 00:59:15,343
Well I gotta go. I'm glad I could help you.

895
00:59:19,376 --> 00:59:20,676
Do you need a ride?

896
00:59:22,608 --> 00:59:23,749
Hey!

897
00:59:27,120 --> 00:59:31,501
Maybe uh... maybe Tommy took it. Your bike.

898
00:59:32,685 --> 00:59:36,280
Tommy doesn't even know how to ride a bike. But
since you brought it up you want me to ask him?

899
00:59:36,281 --> 00:59:37,329
- I...
- No no no no.

900
00:59:37,330 --> 00:59:39,873
Obviously if you think he
took the bike, let me ask him.

901
00:59:39,874 --> 00:59:42,477
- Well I don't mean...
- Hey what's up Johnny?

902
00:59:42,478 --> 00:59:45,119
- Yeah. Wade here says you took my bike. Is that true?
- Um. What?

903
00:59:45,120 --> 00:59:46,544
I can't ride a bike. Remember?

904
00:59:46,545 --> 00:59:48,061
Yeah, no I didn't think
you would have either.

905
00:59:48,062 --> 00:59:50,676
He's trying to frame me? You know what?
Tell that dude I'm done.

906
00:59:50,677 --> 00:59:52,837
- Yeah, I don't blame you.
- This whole film is a mess.

907
00:59:53,024 --> 00:59:55,024
I didn't mean that.

908
00:59:57,840 --> 01:00:00,800
Johnny. I'll help you find your bike.

909
01:00:03,760 --> 01:00:05,560
Yeah sure you will!

910
01:00:05,561 --> 01:00:09,277
- I was late to work 'cause I couldn't find that damn bike.
- I'm sorry Johnny it was for this scene...

911
01:00:09,278 --> 01:00:12,834
- Do you know what it's like to get chewed out by your boss on your third day of your first job?
- Like method acting!

912
01:00:12,835 --> 01:00:14,376
I swear I was going to give it back!

913
01:00:14,640 --> 01:00:18,880
- By the way, Tommy's done with the film. So am I.
- Don't just walk away, we're almost done with the film!

914
01:00:21,600 --> 01:00:24,997
We're almost done with the film.

915
01:00:43,200 --> 01:00:45,661
You think we overreacted?

916
01:00:45,662 --> 01:00:47,025
No, I mean,

917
01:00:47,026 --> 01:00:48,648
The guy's a vampire.

918
01:00:48,649 --> 01:00:50,240
If we were younger I'd say sure,

919
01:00:50,800 --> 01:00:54,181
make up and be all buddy
buddy again, but now?

920
01:00:54,182 --> 01:00:57,584
- I'm 18. I'm going to college soon.
- Yeah, same.

921
01:00:58,000 --> 01:01:02,288
- See, you got to surround yourself with people who'll help you get places.
- Yeah

922
01:01:02,289 --> 01:01:03,440
How'd you do in school?

923
01:01:04,880 --> 01:01:06,594
Not as good for how hard I tried.

924
01:01:06,595 --> 01:01:09,200
Yeah I get you there. How did Wade do?

925
01:01:09,201 --> 01:01:11,132
Amazing actually, he's pretty smart.

926
01:01:11,133 --> 01:01:14,804
And he wants to be a filmmaker? It's
not really fair to the rest of us.

927
01:01:14,805 --> 01:01:16,369
Kind of a waste of talent.

928
01:01:18,400 --> 01:01:20,037
I mean,

929
01:01:20,038 --> 01:01:22,430
I get he was just trying to get the scene,

930
01:01:22,431 --> 01:01:24,973
but to make me late to my real job?

931
01:01:24,974 --> 01:01:26,390
And to blame you for it?

932
01:01:26,391 --> 01:01:28,918
Yeah I mean he's got
drive, I'll give him that.

933
01:01:28,919 --> 01:01:31,167
Yeah but drive too much
and you eventually crash.

934
01:01:33,280 --> 01:01:34,659
What?

935
01:01:34,660 --> 01:01:38,633
Or run out of gas. I mean you get
what I'm trying to say, like...

936
01:02:06,160 --> 01:02:07,583
You good?

937
01:02:08,111 --> 01:02:10,376
Yeah. Just practicing my acting.

938
01:03:25,840 --> 01:03:28,212
Hey kid, remember me?!

939
01:03:28,213 --> 01:03:29,787
How the hell did you guys
find me?

940
01:03:29,788 --> 01:03:32,477
- We followed you home from the park.
- Dude that sounds creepy.

941
01:03:32,478 --> 01:03:39,042
Oh yeah, we uh, uh came from the gym?
Or uh I saw you walking, or?

942
01:03:39,600 --> 01:03:40,677
That makes no sense.

943
01:03:40,678 --> 01:03:42,474
What do you want?

944
01:03:42,475 --> 01:03:44,151
You're gonna pay for what you did.

945
01:03:44,152 --> 01:03:46,553
Cops are already on the way.

946
01:03:46,554 --> 01:03:49,490
Where's your friend, huh?
Guess you'll do for now.

947
01:03:49,491 --> 01:03:51,679
And don't do nothing loco
homes 'cause I'm filming.

948
01:03:51,680 --> 01:03:54,483
- Already took my money!
- Listen, I was just trying to help a friend, I didn't...

949
01:03:54,484 --> 01:03:56,126
Oh, the one who's not here!

950
01:03:56,960 --> 01:03:59,598
- You're outnumbered fool.
- I swear I didn't know what to do.

951
01:03:59,599 --> 01:04:02,488
- Yeah well the cops will know what to do.
- You got your pocket knife?

952
01:04:03,083 --> 01:04:04,522
Nah homes, I left it at home.

953
01:04:04,523 --> 01:04:06,194
Are you kidding me?

954
01:04:06,195 --> 01:04:08,340
- Nah homes, I thought...
- The cops won't even care!

955
01:04:08,341 --> 01:04:10,109
What do you guys want, money?

956
01:04:10,110 --> 01:04:12,506
Nah fool, we did until you jumped us, see?

957
01:04:12,507 --> 01:04:14,528
We don't play like that!

958
01:04:25,120 --> 01:04:29,435
I'm not proud of what I did,
leaving Johnny like that.

959
01:04:29,436 --> 01:04:32,692
It felt like a knife in my back
when I saw him with Tommy earlier.

960
01:04:32,693 --> 01:04:36,501
And I thought leaving him with those
guys would somehow pull out the blade.

961
01:04:37,120 --> 01:04:40,237
But all I ended up doing
was stabbing him too.

962
01:05:04,400 --> 01:05:05,654
Wade...

963
01:05:07,108 --> 01:05:09,614
Wade what are you doing man?

964
01:05:12,480 --> 01:05:14,722
I think I messed up.

965
01:05:15,581 --> 01:05:17,410
What's going on?

966
01:05:28,320 --> 01:05:31,898
I feel like I can't even
protect my own friends anymore.

967
01:05:35,661 --> 01:05:37,640
I should have helped him.

968
01:05:40,880 --> 01:05:41,880
Johnny?

969
01:05:44,160 --> 01:05:46,738
I keep pushing everyone away.

970
01:05:48,560 --> 01:05:50,555
You always got me.

971
01:05:51,348 --> 01:05:52,821
You're not my friend.

972
01:05:54,720 --> 01:05:56,059
Fine.

973
01:05:56,720 --> 01:05:59,370
But I'm your brother and I'm here for you.

974
01:05:59,371 --> 01:06:02,650
- No you're not.
- I'm trying to be

975
01:06:04,720 --> 01:06:08,473
Johnny was more of a brother than you.

976
01:06:08,474 --> 01:06:12,790
He always believed in
me, and now he hates me.

977
01:06:13,517 --> 01:06:16,317
It's not that I don't believe in you Wade.

978
01:06:16,318 --> 01:06:18,595
I'm just trying to be real.

979
01:06:18,596 --> 01:06:21,448
Real friends won't lie just
to make you feel better.

980
01:06:22,307 --> 01:06:24,539
You lie to yourself all the time.

981
01:06:25,600 --> 01:06:26,803
Care to explain?

982
01:06:26,804 --> 01:06:28,886
With your stupid master plan.

983
01:06:28,887 --> 01:06:32,368
Just let go of them Will. We
could have our own futures.

984
01:06:32,369 --> 01:06:37,729
You know what Wade? I'm trying to be
a good big brother and help you out.

985
01:06:37,730 --> 01:06:41,504
It is a stupid move to throw
away what's been given to you.

986
01:06:41,505 --> 01:06:46,083
And if you don't care about
what mom and dad wanted for us,

987
01:06:46,084 --> 01:06:47,672
then you can get out of their house.

988
01:06:47,673 --> 01:06:52,568
Who are you to say what they wanted? You just want to keep the
store because the only part of them that still lives and breathes.

989
01:06:52,569 --> 01:06:55,118
That store gave us everything.

990
01:06:55,119 --> 01:06:57,547
And look at you. You're miserable.

991
01:06:57,548 --> 01:07:01,115
And if I don't follow my dreams, a few
years down the line I'll be miserable too.

992
01:07:01,116 --> 01:07:03,666
I'm not gonna lose you too Wade.

993
01:07:03,667 --> 01:07:06,099
We're gonna stick together.

994
01:07:06,100 --> 01:07:08,429
Lucky for you that's
probably what's gonna happen.

995
01:07:08,430 --> 01:07:11,139
No, it's lucky for you.

996
01:07:11,140 --> 01:07:14,129
I hope you got to live out
your dreams while you could.

997
01:07:14,130 --> 01:07:15,657
Because summer's almost over buddy.

998
01:07:15,658 --> 01:07:17,281
Can't you see what you've been doing to me?

999
01:07:17,282 --> 01:07:21,918
- You planted this seed in my head that all
I'm good for is what's easy for me!
- Get off me!

1000
01:07:24,480 --> 01:07:27,840
You don't know how hard
I've been working for this.

1001
01:07:28,480 --> 01:07:30,132
You don't know what I'm being put through.

1002
01:07:30,133 --> 01:07:31,611
What you're being put through?

1003
01:07:32,480 --> 01:07:33,750
What about me?

1004
01:07:33,751 --> 01:07:35,473
We're the heirs of mom
and dad's liquor store,

1005
01:07:35,474 --> 01:07:38,374
- But all it feels like I've inherited is a poison.
- You want it so bad?

1006
01:07:38,375 --> 01:07:42,083
A poison that runs through my veins eating at my
insides knowing I'll never be able to do what I love.

1007
01:07:42,084 --> 01:07:44,340
You want it that bad?

1008
01:07:45,542 --> 01:07:47,542
Save me a seat at the Oscars, then.

1009
01:07:49,120 --> 01:07:52,400
Being a filmmaker doesn't mean I
have to win Oscars or become famous.

1010
01:07:53,120 --> 01:07:56,838
Plenty of people devote their lives
to it and make a fine living doing it.

1011
01:07:58,080 --> 01:08:00,617
- Because they love it.
- Maybe you're right.

1012
01:08:01,410 --> 01:08:03,147
I'm sorry.

1013
01:08:03,148 --> 01:08:05,469
And I'd do this whole thing myself.

1014
01:08:05,470 --> 01:08:11,260
But I don't have the time to go to college
or to study while I manage the store.

1015
01:08:11,261 --> 01:08:13,395
I need your help.

1016
01:08:13,669 --> 01:08:19,050
The way I see my future is with you beside me and
I'm sorry. It's just too late to change that.

1017
01:08:20,080 --> 01:08:22,704
You can always make films Wade.

1018
01:08:22,705 --> 01:08:25,460
You don't need some
special school to do that.

1019
01:08:25,461 --> 01:08:27,906
I don't need business school
to own a store either.

1020
01:08:27,907 --> 01:08:31,169
That degree will open
more opportunities for us.

1021
01:08:32,320 --> 01:08:34,443
We can start moving our way up.

1022
01:08:34,773 --> 01:08:36,975
There you go with 'we' again.

1023
01:08:38,099 --> 01:08:40,775
'We' are brothers.

1024
01:08:40,776 --> 01:08:45,000
So yeah. We.

1025
01:08:46,836 --> 01:08:51,109
You might not like me,
and you don't have to.

1026
01:08:51,110 --> 01:08:55,315
But I'm gonna be there for you either way
because I made mom and dad a promise, okay?

1027
01:08:55,920 --> 01:09:01,941
When you were adopted, I promised them I
wouldn't let anything bad ever happen to you.

1028
